<parameter name="old_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-22',
    prompt: 'Create a detailed timeline and task list for your first 90 days of active freelancing, including daily marketing activities and weekly client outreach goals',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'A structured launch plan with specific daily and weekly activities is essential for building momentum and accountability during your crucial first months as a freelancer. Break down your first 90 days into weekly goals that include number of proposals to send, networking events to attend, portfolio pieces to create, and social media posts to publish. Having concrete daily actions prevents the paralysis that often comes with the freedom of freelancing while ensuring you\'re consistently working toward building your client base rather than just waiting for opportunities to appear.'
  },
];</parameter>
<parameter name="new_string">  {
    id: 'prompt-22',
    prompt: 'Create a detailed timeline and task list for your first 90 days of active freelancing, including daily marketing activities and weekly client outreach goals',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'A structured launch plan with specific daily and weekly activities is essential for building momentum and accountability during your crucial first months as a freelancer. Break down your first 90 days into weekly goals that include number of proposals to send, networking events to attend, portfolio pieces to create, and social media posts to publish. Having concrete daily actions prevents the paralysis that often comes with the freedom of freelancing while ensuring you\'re consistently working toward building your client base rather than just waiting for opportunities to appear.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-23',
    prompt: 'Research and document backup plan options for lean periods by identifying 3 income streams you can activate when client work is slow',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Creative freelancing naturally includes feast-or-famine cycles, so having predetermined backup income strategies prevents financial stress and hasty decision-making during slow periods. Identify options like part-time creative roles, teaching workshops, selling digital products, or offering simplified services at lower price points that you can quickly activate when needed. Planning these alternatives while business is good allows you to make strategic choices rather than desperate ones, maintaining your professional standards while ensuring financial stability throughout the ups and downs of freelance life.'
  },
];</parameter>
</invoke>
